images.name: Romeo Doubs makes shoestring catch to seal Packers win
images.caption: Jordan Love ropes one to Romeo Doubs, who somehow hangs onto the ball for a Packers touchdown.

articles.description: — Jordan Love threw two touchdown passes to Romeo Doubs and the Green Bay Packers ended Seattle's four-game winning streak with a 30-13 victory Sunday night over the Seahawks, who lost quarterback Geno Smith to a knee injury.
articles.headline: Jordan Love throws for 2 TDs and Packers beat Seahawks 30-13 as Seattle QB Geno Smith injures knee

images.name: commanders for troll [608x342]
images.caption: The Washington Commanders trolled the New Orleans Saints multiple times after their win.

images.name: Commanders hang on after Saints' failed 2-point conversion
images.caption: Spencer Rattler's touchdown pass to Foster Moreau makes it a one-point game, but the 2-point conversion is no good, giving the Commanders a 20-19 win.

articles.description: There were a handful of close finishes in Week 15 of the NFL season, prompting petty posts around the league.
articles.headline: Commanders' jabs at Saints top NFL Week 15 trolls

images.name: Josh Allen bolsters MVP case with 4 TDs vs. Lions
images.caption: Josh Allen has a night to remember as he throws two touchdowns and runs in another two in a statement win over the Lions for the Bills.
